Arricano Seeks Capital Boost From Goldman Sachs, Aeripaeev Says

-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 
2011-06-14T08:21:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-14/arricano-seeks-capital-boost-from-goldman-sachs-aeripaeev-says.html
Arricano Trading Ltd., a retail
property developer in Ukraine, is in talks with Goldman Sachs
Group Inc. and other potential investors to increase its share
capital by $70 million to $250 million this year,  Aeripaeev 
reported, citing Estonian businessman Hillar Teder, Arricano’s
main owner.  Goldman Sachs may invest as much as $40 million, Teder was
cited as saying in an interview. Teder’s investment vehicle,
Expert Capital, owns 83 percent of Arricano and  Dragon-Ukrainian
Properties & Development Plc (DUPD)  has a minority stake.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
 oummelas@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  